From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0051/N] skip libawt and libattach native builds on bsd target

Build70 cleared mlib_image (0050 reserved[1] fix) and reached libawt
(java.desktop AWT native lib) and libattach (jdk.attach native lib).

libawt: shared `Blit.c` -> `unix/native/common/awt/utility/rect.h`
includes `<X11/Xlib.h>`. CheriBSD sysroot has no X11 headers. Even
with `--enable-headless-only`, the base LIBAWT compiles non-X11
files that drag in X11 headers transitively. The AWT graphics code
has multiple platform-specific paths (Linux X11, macOS Quartz,
Windows GDI) -- a real bsd port is a future project.

libattach: SetupJdkLibrary scans per-OS source dirs and finds none
for bsd ("No sources found for BUILD_LIBATTACH"). The attach API
needs platform-specific process attach (Linux /proc, Solaris doors,
etc.); we don't need it for `java -version`.

Phase 1 goal is bring-up: get the JVM running on FVP, validate the
CHERI port. Both libawt and libattach are non-essential for that.
Skip their native builds on bsd. java.desktop and jdk.attach Java
sources still compile (they're OS-agnostic); the LoadLibrary calls
fail lazily at first use, which is fine -- `java -version` doesn't
hit either path.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0051)

--- a/make/modules/java.desktop/Lib.gmk
+++ b/make/modules/java.desktop/Lib.gmk
@@ -35,7 +35,13 @@ $(call FillFindCache, $(wildcard $(TOPDIR)/src/java.desktop/*/native))
 ################################################################################
 # Create the AWT/2D libraries
 
+# Phase 1: skip libawt et al on bsd target. The graphics native code has
+# unconditional X11/Quartz dependencies and Phase 1 only needs core JDK
+# (java -version etc.). java.desktop Java sources still compile; native
+# loadLibrary will fail at first AWT use, fine for Phase 1.
+ifneq ($(call isTargetOs, bsd), true)
 include lib/Awt2dLibraries.gmk
+endif
 
 ################################################################################
 # Create the libjsound library
diff --git a/make/modules/jdk.attach/Lib.gmk b/make/modules/jdk.attach/Lib.gmk
index 6c61926b804..4d060b5c94e 100644
--- a/make/modules/jdk.attach/Lib.gmk
+++ b/make/modules/jdk.attach/Lib.gmk
@@ -34,6 +34,10 @@ ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, windows), true)
   LIBATTACH_CFLAGS := -DPSAPI_VERSION=1
 endif
 
+# Phase 1: no bsd source dir for libattach; skip the native build on bsd.
+# Java attach API requires the native lib for cross-process attach, which is
+# not needed for headless boot.
+ifneq ($(call isTargetOs, bsd), true)
 $(eval $(call SetupJdkLibrary, BUILD_LIBATTACH, \
     NAME := attach, \
     OPTIMIZATION := LOW, \
@@ -48,5 +52,6 @@ $(eval $(call SetupJdkLibrary, BUILD_LIBATTACH, \
 $(BUILD_LIBATTACH): $(call FindLib, java.base, java)
 
 TARGETS += $(BUILD_LIBATTACH)
+endif
 
 ################################################################################
